          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Think of it as try-before-you-buy. You see your full fit-out in 3D — cabinetry, drawers, sleeping setup, kitchen, power and water placement — before we cut a single piece. It catches mistakes early and lets you tweak the layout until you're 100% happy. It's cheaper and faster to change a 3D model than a physical build, so you never end up saying "next time I'd do it differently."
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Why laminated plywood instead of aluminium?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            It's lighter than most people think, easier to work with, and absorbs vibrations instead of amplifying them — so no rattling on corrugations. Every piece is CNC-cut to millimetre precision, so the fit is perfect every time. It gives a warmer, more liveable interior compared to metal, and it's easier to modify later if your setup changes.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            What finishes and colours are available?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            After your 3D design is approved, you choose from three finish levels. <strong>All Laminate</strong> — laminated plywood drawer fronts and tops in white, black, timber or green. <strong>Hybrid</strong> — laminated plywood drawer fronts with marine carpet tops and sliding bed. <strong>Full Carpet</strong> — marine carpet drawer fronts, tops, sliding bed and gull wings. Marine carpet comes in any colour — black, grey, beige and dark navy are the most popular. We can also do a raw plywood finish for the natural look. All exposed plywood surfaces are hand-lacquered as standard to prevent moisture damage.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Can I remove the fit-out without damaging my vehicle?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Yes. We use factory bolt holes wherever possible. If we need to add mounting points, we use rivets that are painted and rust-proofed before installation. Once the fit-out is removed, you're left with a few small holes that look like factory bolt holes — easy to cover with a bolt until you want the fit-out back in.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            What's the deposit and payment process?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Three stages. A $500 deposit kicks off the 3D design process — that covers the labour to model your fit-out. Once you approve the design and commit to the build, there's a materials deposit (roughly 60% of the build cost). The remaining balance is paid when you pick up the vehicle and you're happy with everything.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Do I own the 3D designs?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            No. The $500 deposit covers the labour to design your fit-out. You get to view, review and approve the 3D model, but the design files remain Bushbound's intellectual property. We don't sell or share 3D models.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Do you offer warranty on your builds?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            12-month warranty on all craftsmanship. Electrical components and appliances carry their manufacturer's warranty — for example, Victron is 5 years, Bushman fridges are 7 years. If something isn't right, we'll sort it out.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            What power system do I need?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Depends on how you travel. Our minimum recommendation is 200Ah of lithium — that'll cover weekend getaways comfortably (100Ah drains too fast). If you want creature comforts like a coffee machine, microwave or air fryer, we offer inverter setups too. Our primary offering is 12V. 24V and 48V systems are available in our custom tier, installed by a certified auto electrician. All electrical work across every build is done by a certified auto sparky — fully compliant and insurance-covered.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Can I add to my fit-out later?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Yes. Small modifications and additions go through the same 3D design process and are quoted separately. For major changes, we normally recommend selling the existing fit-out — someone else would love to have it — and starting fresh with exactly what you want. Plenty of our customers sell their fit-out with the old car and come back for a new build.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-stone-dark/10 overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-charcoal hover:text-primary transition-colors">
            Do you provide a loaner vehicle during the build?
